        "collapsible_row_A9Grx6": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often should I replace my mattress?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Most mattresses should be replaced every 7-10 years, depending on the type and quality. Signs it’s time for a replacement include sagging, discomfort, and waking up with aches.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_7gcYJB": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is the best mattress for back pain?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Memory foam and hybrid mattresses are often recommended for back pain because they provide excellent support and contouring. Learn more in our blog: <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/tips/best-mattresses-for-back-pain\">Best Mattresses for Back Pain</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_TNHajB": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do I need a box spring for my mattress?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>It depends on the type of mattress and bed frame you have. Many modern mattresses, such as memory foam or latex, work well on platform beds without a box spring.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_Me7Tmb": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What firmness level should I choose?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>The right firmness depends on your sleeping position and body weight. Side sleepers often prefer softer mattresses, while back and stomach sleepers benefit from medium to firm options. Check out our blog on <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/tips/choosing-the-right-firmness\">choosing the right firmness</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_LWVCpb": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are mattresses with cooling technologies worth it?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>If you’re a hot sleeper, cooling technologies such as gel-infused memory foam or breathable hybrids can significantly improve your comfort.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_nG7Gpx": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I return a mattress if I don’t like it?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes, most of our mattresses come with a trial period. Check our <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/pages/trial-period-policy\">trial period policy</a> for details.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_LX68Ri": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are latex mattresses good for allergies?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes, latex mattresses are naturally hypoallergenic and resistant to dust mites, mold, and bacteria, making them an excellent choice for allergy sufferers.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_kMqPGd": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I clean and maintain my mattress?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Use a mattress protector to prevent stains and dust buildup. Regularly vacuum your mattress and rotate it every 3-6 months to prolong its lifespan. Read more on <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/how-to-user-guide/how-to-clean-a-mattress-a-complete-guide?_pos=1&_sid=6f735409c&_ss=r\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/how-to-user-guide/how-to-clean-a-mattress-a-complete-guide?_pos=1&_sid=6f735409c&_ss=r\">How to Clean a Mattress: A Complete Guide</a></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_gHmYDY": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does sleep boost immunity and overall health?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Getting sufficient high-quality sleep strengthens your immune system by allowing the body to produce infection-fighting cells and proteins. Sleep also helps regulate stress hormones, reduce inflammation, and improve recovery from illnesses. To maintain a strong immune system, aim for 7-9 hours of sleep per night. Learn more in our blog: <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/health-sleep-wellness/how-sleep-boosts-immunity-for-better-health\">How Sleep Boosts Immunity for Better Health</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_3Jw6tN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does sleep impact weight management?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Sleep plays a significant role in weight management by regulating hormones that control hunger and appetite. Poor sleep increases levels of ghrelin (hunger hormone) and decreases leptin (satiety hormone), making it harder to resist overeating. Additionally, lack of sleep affects metabolism and energy levels, leading to reduced physical activity and higher calorie consumption. To maintain a healthy weight, aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep nightly. Learn more in our blog: <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/health-sleep-wellness/the-role-of-sleep-in-weight-management\">The Role of Sleep in Weight Management</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_mBNgwy": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does sleep affect mental health?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Sleep and mental health are closely linked. Quality sleep helps regulate mood, improve cognitive function, and reduce stress. Chronic sleep deprivation can increase the risk of anxiety, depression, and other mental health disorders. Creating a consistent sleep schedule and choosing a comfortable, supportive mattress can significantly improve mental well-being. Learn more in our blog: <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/health-sleep-wellness/sleep-and-mental-health-what-you-need-to-know\">Sleep and Mental Health: What You Need to Know</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_CPg6c4": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can buying a new mattress improve your quality of life?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Absolutely! A new mattress can significantly improve your quality of life by enhancing sleep quality, reducing aches and pains, and boosting overall well-being. The right mattress provides proper spinal alignment and reduces pressure points, helping you wake up refreshed and energized. Learn more in our blog: <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/blogs/health-sleep-wellness/can-buying-a-new-mattress-improve-your-quality-of-life\">Can Buying a New Mattress Improve Your Quality of Life?</a>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
